summary: So, apparently, Captain Marvel - The Official Movie Special confirms that Yon-Rogg is not as strawman-like and one-dimensional...
body:
So, apparently, Captain Marvel - The Official Movie Special confirms that Yon-Rogg is not as strawman-like and one-dimensional as seems. Not all is solely manipulation.

“They have a tight bond, but Vers’ humanity still comes out, and I think that is hugely attractive to Yon-Rogg. I think he finds her irresistible, and it’s her human elements that he really warms to.” - Law. 

Seems like he sincerely likes Carol as a person after all. That’s canon for you.
Still a bastard for what he did, but not an empty, unfeeling one. 

That’s a twist. That’s very twisty. (not)

body:
Captain Marvel - Avengers Endgame theories!!!

Okay so I JUST watched Captain marvel for the second time and this is what I noticed:

When Carol changes the colour of her suit with Monica, she tries different colours at first BUT those represent other heroes??

She tries Red-Gold at first, that’s clearly Iron man.

Second is Green-Gold which is Loki.

Third one was the rainbow which stands for the Bifrost.

And the last one was Green-Silver, Hulks colours!!

COINCIDENCE?? I THINK NOT!!!!

so like the rumors about Endgame are already similar, Tony is a major thing, Loki is not dead and Hulk is .. refusing to come back.

Talk to me guys.

Hi. I'm Birdie and I'm a stage manager who occasionally wishes she was about a billion other things including but not limited to a musician, a writer, a dancer, a photographer, a chef, and a full-time traveler.

Due Tumblr's new regulations making it harder to figure out if new followers are actual people or bots, if you want to follow me, send me a message. Otherwise I'm blocking you outright. I don't bite, I promise.

This is a blog mostly for my fandom flailings (Hannibal, Agents of SHIELD, Marvel Cinematic Universe, Star Wars, Lord of the Rings, Newsroom) and for putting my writing and photography where it is more easily found. There also may or may not be a smattering of recipes, music, and oddities interesting to no one but me.

If you're interested in fanfiction for Hannibal, AoS, MCU, and Newsroom, find me under the handle Hesterbyrde on AO3.

If you're interested in classical music, my music blog is @mygrandmotherspiano. If you're into Hannibal, I'm over at @drowningortolan, and if you're looking for Star Wars I'm @12porgsinablackrobe.

summary: About 30 min ago, I came home after having watched Captain Marvel and like most others, I’ll write a bit about it, might contain...
body:
About 30 min ago, I came home after having watched Captain Marvel and like most others, I’ll write a bit about it, might contain spoilers, so I’ll put it under a read more (in case I’m not the last one to watch it).

First of all, did I like the movie? Yes. Yes, I did.

Did it make me exited? Unfortunately, not.

Did I like Carol? Yeah, I did.

Am I happy there’s a female Marvel superhero movie? Of course.

Do I still wish they would’ve chosen another female hero? Yes.

They had, thankfully, made Carol more likeable in the movies than she’s been in the comics I’ve read and in animated shows. I think that’s part of the reason I didn’t get exited by this movie in the way I have about the others (because I’m not fond of Carol in the comics), though another reason is that I know this brings us closer to Endgame and I don’t want that.

Carol is one of the characters that makes most sense out of context to make a movie about, but there is others, like Jennifer Walters aka She-Hulk or actually given Scarlet Witch the powers she is supposed to have (she can bend reality and a lot of other powerful crazy shit. Then there’s Ms Marvel, America Chavez, Rescue (aka Pepper Potts), female Thor (aka Jane Foster), Spectrum etc. But yeah, I do get why they choose Carol Danvers, but that doesn’t mean I wouldn’t have preferred another character.

Favourite character in the movie: Goose

Most emotional part: Not exactly part of the movie, but the Marvel intro and the first post-credit scene.
